WEBVTT

01:45.750 --> 01:47.834
Dexter:
PREVIOUSLY ON "DEXTER"...

01:47.834 --> 01:49.875
IF YOU WERE
THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER,

01:49.875 --> 01:51.333
WOULD YOU USE
A PLACE LIKE THIS?

01:51.333 --> 01:53.959
THE CONDITIONS IN THIS SPACE
DON'T SUPPORT HIS M.O.

01:53.959 --> 01:56.000
MAYBE THE BUTCHER'S
HAVING AN IDENTITY CRISIS.

01:56.000 --> 01:57.166
YOUR BROTHER'S A JUNKIE.

01:57.166 --> 01:59.917
ARE YOU  HIGH? HE'S NEVER
EVEN SMOKED A CIGARETTE.

01:59.917 --> 02:01.583
Gail: LOOKS LIKE CODY'S
ENJOYING HIMSELF.

02:01.583 --> 02:03.250
DEXTER'S VERY PATIENT
WITH HIM.

02:03.250 --> 02:04.583
DEXTER'S A SAINT.

02:04.583 --> 02:06.625
I WAS HOPING YOU COULD DIG UP
AN OLD CASE FILE FOR ME.

02:06.625 --> 02:07.959
GOT A DATE?

02:07.959 --> 02:09.959
IT'S THE CRIME SCENE
WHERE HARRY FOUND ME.

02:09.959 --> 02:11.208
Harry: HOW MUCH?

02:11.208 --> 02:12.959
Woman: 300 BRICKS,
GIVE OR TAKE.

02:12.959 --> 02:15.458
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR A CHANCE
TO TAKE YOUR ASS OUT.

02:15.458 --> 02:17.083
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL,
SERGEANT.

02:17.083 --> 02:19.709
HE CROSSED THE LINE, LIEUTENANT.
HE BROKE INTO MY LAB.

02:19.709 --> 02:21.250
HE'S PROBABLY GONNA START
TAILING ME AGAIN.

02:21.250 --> 02:23.166
SERGEANT DOAKES TAILED YOU?

02:23.166 --> 02:24.250
I FOLLOWED HIM
TO AN N.A. MEETING.

02:24.250 --> 02:25.875
THAT ASSHOLE
LIED ABOUT THAT, TOO.

02:25.875 --> 02:27.542
YOU'RE OBSESSED.
I'M NOT.

02:27.542 --> 02:28.750
AND I NEED YOU TO SEE IT!

02:28.750 --> 02:31.250
DINNER WAS FANTASTIC,
RITA. WOW.

02:31.250 --> 02:32.333
I KIND OF LIKE HER.

02:32.333 --> 02:34.083
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]
[ Beep ]

02:34.083 --> 02:35.583
Lila: Dex,
just calling to check in.

02:35.583 --> 02:37.250
Imagine Rita's face
if I told her

02:37.250 --> 02:39.709
that you and I had spent
the night together in a hotel.

02:39.709 --> 02:40.875
IT'S OVER, DEXTER.

02:40.875 --> 02:43.917
I GUESS I JUST HOPE WITH LUNDY
IT WILL BE DIFFERENT.

02:43.917 --> 02:45.542
WHY?
I RESPECT HIM.

02:45.542 --> 02:46.792
YOU LOVE  HIM.

02:46.792 --> 02:49.166
NO. HE'S LIKE MY DAD.

02:49.166 --> 02:51.000
YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:51.000 --> 02:53.500
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO SAID I'M
SUPPOSED TO FEEL MY FEELINGS!

02:53.500 --> 02:55.709
WELL, NOW I'M TELLING YOU
TO GET THEM UNDER CONTROL!

02:55.709 --> 02:57.291
[ GASPS ]

03:05.458 --> 03:07.166
WHICH STEP WAS THAT?

03:07.166 --> 03:08.709
[ LAUGHS ]

03:19.834 --> 03:23.917
Lila:
USE THE ENTIRE CANVAS.

03:23.917 --> 03:28.375
START FROM THE TOP.
WORK YOUR WAY DOWN.

03:28.375 --> 03:32.667
LIGHT, FEATHERY STROKES.

03:32.667 --> 03:34.542
PERFECT!

03:34.542 --> 03:35.959
STUNNING.

03:35.959 --> 03:39.792
TRY LONGER STROKES NOW.

03:39.792 --> 03:41.750
PERFECT.

03:43.125 --> 03:45.250
[ GRUNTING ]

03:45.250 --> 03:47.041
MMM!

03:47.041 --> 03:49.375
[ GROANING ]

03:51.750 --> 03:53.375
[ MOANING ]

03:58.709 --> 04:00.375
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

04:00.375 --> 04:02.583
YOU REALLY KNOW WHAT YOU WANT,
DON'T YOU?

04:07.000 --> 04:10.542
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

04:10.542 --> 04:12.625
SOME MEN DO.

04:12.625 --> 04:14.583
NO.

04:14.583 --> 04:18.417
I'VE ALWAYS FOUND
INSTRUCTION MANUALS...

04:18.417 --> 04:19.750
QUITE USEFUL.

04:19.750 --> 04:21.375
[ LAUGHS ]

04:25.458 --> 04:28.875
OKAY, YOUR TURN.

04:30.166 --> 04:32.375
WHAT DO YOU  WANT?

04:36.375 --> 04:38.625
I THINK THAT WAS IT.

04:38.625 --> 04:42.250
HMM, COME ON.

04:42.250 --> 04:46.250
YOU MUST HAVE
SOME DARK FANTASIES...

04:48.417 --> 04:52.166
...UNFULFILLED URGES.

04:52.166 --> 04:55.625
I'M PRETTY GOOD
AT ACTING ON THOSE.

04:55.625 --> 04:58.834
REALLY?

04:58.834 --> 05:01.000
THEN FUCK ME LIKE THAT.

05:15.667 --> 05:18.458
YOUR LIGHT'S BURNED OUT.

05:18.458 --> 05:20.125
IT'S THE WIRING.

05:20.125 --> 05:24.875
I'VE BEEN ASKING MY LANDLORD
TO FIX IT FOR WEEKS.

05:24.875 --> 05:26.125
[ GIGGLES ]

05:26.125 --> 05:29.250
WELL, NOW I CAN SEE BETTER.

05:29.250 --> 05:31.834
THAT'S WHERE
MY LANDLORD LIVES.

05:31.834 --> 05:33.625
NOW HE'LL HAVE TO FIX IT.

05:33.625 --> 05:35.959
MMM.

05:35.959 --> 05:37.959
SEE YOU LATER.

05:42.458 --> 05:47.834
GOT TO ADMIRE LILA FOR TAKING
THINGS INTO HER OWN HANDS.

05:47.834 --> 05:49.792
THAT INCLUDES ME.

05:53.959 --> 05:56.667
OHH. MOM. [ SIGHS ]

05:56.667 --> 05:59.291
COME ON, LET'S GO!
NO MORE MOPING.

05:59.291 --> 06:01.542
I'M NOT MOPING.
I'M SLEEPING.

06:01.542 --> 06:03.500
OVERSLEEPING --
THIRD TIME THIS WEEK.

06:03.500 --> 06:05.333
THE ONLY WAY YOU'RE GONNA
GET OVER DEXTER

06:05.333 --> 06:08.500
IS IF YOU TAKE CHARGE
OF YOUR DAY.

06:08.500 --> 06:09.500
[ GROANS ]

06:09.500 --> 06:11.709
COME ON. YOU'RE NOT
IN HIGH SCHOOL ANYMORE.

06:11.709 --> 06:16.875
GO SCRUB YOUR FACE,
AND I'LL HEAT UP SOME OATMEAL.

06:16.875 --> 06:19.417
[ SIGHS ]

06:24.208 --> 06:27.041
DIDN'T HEAR YOU
COME IN LAST NIGHT.

06:27.041 --> 06:30.709
WELL, IT WAS LATE.
I WAS QUIET.

06:30.709 --> 06:32.959
YEAH,
YOU'RE GOOD AT QUIET.

06:32.959 --> 06:35.375
GUESS YOU KIND OF HAVE TO BE
WITH ME CRASHING HERE

06:35.375 --> 06:38.250
AND RITA'S MOM OVER THERE.

06:38.250 --> 06:40.542
YOU AND RITA
FUCK QUIET, TOO?

06:40.542 --> 06:43.041
AND SHE'S OFF,
RIGHT OUT OF THE GATE.

06:43.041 --> 06:45.500
BECAUSE ME --
I WAKE THE GODDAMN DEAD.

06:45.500 --> 06:46.750
IT'S A PROBLEM.

06:46.750 --> 06:48.417
OH, I KNOW,
ONLY TOO WELL.

06:48.417 --> 06:49.792
SCARY, RIGHT?

06:49.792 --> 06:51.959
SOMETIMES I DISTURB MYSELF.

06:51.959 --> 06:55.083
SO [CHUCKLES] WHAT KIND
OF NOISES DOES RITA MAKE?

06:55.083 --> 06:58.417
COULD WE NOT TALK
ABOUT SEX...

06:58.417 --> 06:59.792
OR RITA?

06:59.792 --> 07:02.417
WHY?

07:04.250 --> 07:06.417
'CAUSE WE BROKE UP...

07:06.417 --> 07:08.917
FOR REAL.

07:08.917 --> 07:12.417
IT'S OVER.

07:12.417 --> 07:15.750
YOU BREAK UP,
YOU GET BACK TOGETHER --

07:15.750 --> 07:17.083
THAT'S JUST WHAT GOES ON.

07:17.083 --> 07:19.000
I MEAN,
YOU AND RITA ARE FOREVER.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.834
JUST SAY YOU'RE SORRY
AND SEND SOME FUCKING FLOWERS.

07:21.834 --> 07:23.291
YOU'RE NOT HEARING ME.

07:25.417 --> 07:27.917
LOOK,
WHEN ALL THIS BLOWS OVER,

07:27.917 --> 07:31.417
I'LL SPEND A FEW DAYS
AT GABRIEL'S, AND...

07:31.417 --> 07:34.542
YOU CAN SCREW RITA
AS LOUD AS YOU WANT.

07:46.875 --> 07:48.333
BIG NEWS, DEX.

07:48.333 --> 07:50.208
WHOA! FEEL LIKE I GOT CAUGHT
IN A WAVE.

07:50.208 --> 07:54.125
THE MIAMI TRIBUNE  RECEIVED
A 32-PAGE MANIFESTO IN THE MAIL.

07:54.125 --> 07:56.417
IT'S LOOKING GOOD
FOR THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER.

07:56.417 --> 07:58.500
WELL, I'VE HEARD
THAT ONE BEFORE.

07:58.500 --> 07:59.792
LOOK, THIS MAY BE LEGIT.

07:59.792 --> 08:02.583
THE MANIFESTO INCLUDES THE NAMES
OF THREE VICTIMS

08:02.583 --> 08:04.625
WE NEVER RELEASED
TO THE PRESS.

08:04.625 --> 08:07.166
OH, THAT IS BIG NEWS.

08:07.166 --> 08:09.834
I'M HEADING OVER TO THE TRIBUNE
NOW FOR SPECIAL AGENT LUNDY.

08:09.834 --> 08:12.125
HE PUT ME IN CHARGE
OF THE TEAM.

08:12.125 --> 08:13.125
GO, ANGEL.

08:13.125 --> 08:16.166
YEAH, I'M PSYCHED.

08:16.166 --> 08:20.625
YEAH, ME TOO.
I'M ABOUT TO BE PUBLISHED.

08:20.625 --> 08:23.792
I SENT THAT MANIFESTO
TO THE  TRIBUNE.

08:23.792 --> 08:27.166
GUESS I'VE BEEN TAKING
SOME CUES FROM LILA LATELY,

08:27.166 --> 08:28.792
AND NOT JUST IN BED.

08:28.792 --> 08:32.250
I'M TIRED OF  REACTING
TO THE MOVES OF AGENT LUNDY

08:32.250 --> 08:34.000
AND HIS SUPER POSSE.

08:34.000 --> 08:37.333
TIME TO CONTROL  THEIR  ACTIONS
FOR A CHANGE.

08:55.291 --> 08:57.709
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

08:59.834 --> 09:03.458
BETSY COURT, 16.
BLUNT-FORCE BEATING.

09:03.458 --> 09:05.375
IT LOOKS LIKE
SHE WAS SUNNING HERSELF

09:05.375 --> 09:06.625
AND NEVER SAW IT COMING.

09:06.625 --> 09:08.125
WHO CALLED IN THE BODY?

09:08.125 --> 09:13.709
CRAIG WILSON, THE STEPFATHER.
HE'S RIGHT OVER THERE.

09:16.333 --> 09:18.333
WILSON TOLD
THE REPORTING OFFICER

09:18.333 --> 09:21.959
THAT HE CAME HOME FOR LUNCH
AND FOUND HER THAT WAY.

09:21.959 --> 09:24.375
UM, YOU AND DEXTER
RESOLVE YOUR ISSUES?

09:24.375 --> 09:25.500
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED.

09:25.500 --> 09:27.834
WHY? THE BITCH COME CRYING
TO YOU AGAIN?

09:27.834 --> 09:28.917
NO.

09:28.917 --> 09:30.542
THERE'S BLOOD WORK
TO BE DONE HERE,

09:30.542 --> 09:31.959
AND IF YOU CAN'T
CONTROL YOURSELF,

09:31.959 --> 09:33.625
I NEED TO CALL IN
ANOTHER DETECTIVE.

09:33.625 --> 09:35.709
I WON'T SAY ANYTHING TO HURT
THE LITTLE GIRL'S FEELINGS.

09:35.709 --> 09:37.458
GOD DAMN IT, JAMES,
I'M NOT JOKING.

09:37.458 --> 09:38.667
DO I LOOK LIKE
I'M LAUGHING?

09:38.667 --> 09:41.417
NO. YOU DON'T. I WISH YOU WOULD.
YOU USED TO.

09:41.417 --> 09:43.208
BULLSHIT.
I NEVER LAUGHED.

09:43.208 --> 09:46.166
[ SCOFFS ] YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.

09:46.166 --> 09:49.083
NOW, LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA TRY
TO SCARE YOU ANYMORE.

09:49.083 --> 09:51.250
THE REALITY IS,
YOU'RE OUT OF FREE PASSES.

09:51.250 --> 09:53.250
NOW, I ALREADY STOPPED DEXTER
FROM FILING A COMPLAINT

09:53.250 --> 09:54.750
AGAINST YOU ONCE.

09:54.750 --> 09:57.208
I NEVER ASKED YOU
TO DO THAT, MARIA.
WELL, I DID IT,

09:57.208 --> 09:59.750
OUT OF MY OWN CONCERN
OVER YOUR OBSESSIVE BEHAVIOR.

09:59.750 --> 10:01.417
NOW I'M ON THE LINE,

10:01.417 --> 10:03.166
SO IF YOU BULLY DEXTER
IN ANY WAY --

10:03.166 --> 10:04.583
IF YOU EVEN
LOOK AT HIM WRONG,

10:04.583 --> 10:06.125
I WILL NOT BE RESPONSIBLE
FOR THE FALLOUT.

10:06.125 --> 10:07.667
YOU GOT IT?

10:07.667 --> 10:08.625
I GOT IT.

10:08.625 --> 10:11.542
YOU'RE BACKING
THE FUCKING FREAKTARD.

10:11.542 --> 10:13.041
JAMES.

10:23.750 --> 10:26.667
WHERE YOU BEEN, DEXTER?

10:26.667 --> 10:28.875
YOU DON'T BRING ME
DOUGHNUTS.

10:28.875 --> 10:32.125
YOU DON'T SING ME LOVE SONGS.
HOW ARE YOU, CAMILLA?

10:32.125 --> 10:34.291
[ SIGHS ]

10:34.291 --> 10:36.125
I'VE BEEN BETTER.

10:36.125 --> 10:38.291
WELL,
THAT DOESN'T SOUND GOOD.

10:40.792 --> 10:43.125
[ SIGHS ]

10:43.125 --> 10:46.583
SERGEANT DOAKES DROPPED BY
MY FILE ROOM YESTERDAY.

10:46.583 --> 10:48.625
HE REQUESTED THE CASE FILES

10:48.625 --> 10:50.959
FOR THE 1973
SHIPPING-YARD MURDERS.

10:50.959 --> 10:53.041
I GAVE HIM THE SAME LINE
I GAVE YOU

10:53.041 --> 10:54.959
WHEN YOU CAME
SNIFFING AROUND,

10:54.959 --> 10:56.542
SAID ALL THAT OLD STUFF
WAS BOXED UP

10:56.542 --> 10:58.792
IN THE BASEMENT
OF CITY HALL.

10:58.792 --> 11:02.458
THAT MADE HIM REAL ANGRY.

11:02.458 --> 11:04.542
HE SCARED ME, DEXTER.

11:04.542 --> 11:08.208
THAT'S NOT RIGHT.
HE SHOULDN'T DO THAT.

11:08.208 --> 11:12.583
LOOK, DEX, I ALWAYS ASSUMED
THAT YOUR FATHER ASKED ME

11:12.583 --> 11:15.750
TO DESTROY THOSE FILES
TO PROTECT YOU.

11:15.750 --> 11:19.166
NOW I'M NOT SURE
WHAT'S GOING ON.

11:19.166 --> 11:20.333
CAMILLA...

11:20.333 --> 11:22.458
NOW,
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

11:22.458 --> 11:25.250
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO GET FIRED.

11:25.250 --> 11:27.166
I'M RETIRING NEXT YEAR.
DID I TELL YOU?

11:27.166 --> 11:31.000
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FORWARD
TO STAYING HOME WITH GENE.

11:31.000 --> 11:34.041
YOU WON'T LOSE YOUR RETIREMENT.
I WON'T LET THAT HAPPEN.

11:34.041 --> 11:37.500
I CAN STALL SERGEANT DOAKES
FOR A FEW DAYS,

11:37.500 --> 11:40.125
BUT EVENTUALLY,
HE'LL FIGURE OUT

11:40.125 --> 11:42.208
THAT THAT CASE FILE'S MISSING,
JUST LIKE YOU DID.

11:42.208 --> 11:45.125
AND HE'LL TRACK IT BACK TO ME,
YOU KNOW, JUST LIKE YOU DID.

11:45.125 --> 11:48.792
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THIS.
YOU HAVE MY WORD.

11:54.542 --> 11:56.542
SO MUCH FOR THREATENING DOAKES.

11:56.542 --> 12:00.375
HE WON'T BACK OFF TILL
HE EXPOSES THE TWISTED BRANCHES

12:00.375 --> 12:02.083
OF MY FAMILY TREE,

12:02.083 --> 12:05.041
FROM MY FATHER'S INDISCRETIONS
TO MY MURDEROUS BROTHER

12:05.041 --> 12:09.542
TO THE ROOT OF ALL EVIL -- ME.

12:12.834 --> 12:15.166
[ LIGHT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING ]

12:23.125 --> 12:24.583
HEY.

12:24.583 --> 12:26.750
WHY AREN'T YOU
AT THE TRIBUNE?

12:26.750 --> 12:28.583
WHAT FOR?

12:28.583 --> 12:31.709
OUR GUY'S NOT GONNA LEAVE
DNA EVIDENCE ON A DOCUMENT.

12:31.709 --> 12:33.250
OH, BUT THE THRILL
OF THE HUNT.

12:33.250 --> 12:34.709
I'VE HAD
THAT PARTICULAR THRILL.

12:34.709 --> 12:36.000
I'LL LEAVE IT
TO YOUNGER MEN.

12:36.000 --> 12:39.500
BESIDES, IT'S EASIER FOR ME
TO DO MY PART FROM HERE.

12:39.500 --> 12:41.208
YEAH?
WHAT PART IS THAT?

12:41.208 --> 12:46.583
OPERATING ON FAVORS,
POLITICAL LEANINGS, POSTURING.

12:48.125 --> 12:50.959
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO FIND
THE RIGHT MUSIC.

12:52.625 --> 12:53.750
RIGHT.

12:53.750 --> 12:55.583
SO, I'M OFF DUTY TODAY,

12:55.583 --> 12:58.083
BUT HERE ARE THOSE
MARINA REPORTS.

12:58.083 --> 13:00.041
AND AFTER MY WORKOUT,

13:00.041 --> 13:03.291
I'LL SWING BY AND PICK UP A COPY
OF THE MANIFESTO.

13:03.291 --> 13:05.667
LOOK AT THAT BOARD.

13:05.667 --> 13:09.834
THESE KILLS ARE PRECISE,
BUT THERE'S ALSO A FLUIDITY,

13:09.834 --> 13:12.291
EVEN SOME IMPROVISATION.

13:12.291 --> 13:16.375
IF I COULD JUST FIND
THE MUSIC...

13:16.375 --> 13:19.250
WANT TO BORROW MY iPod?

13:20.792 --> 13:22.458
GOT ANY CHOPIN?

13:22.458 --> 13:25.959
NO.
FRESH OUT OF CHOPIN.

13:25.959 --> 13:29.959
SHIT.
CHOPIN'S PERFECT.

13:29.959 --> 13:31.542
DID YOU JUST SWEAR?

13:31.542 --> 13:33.125
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT CAN I SAY?

13:33.125 --> 13:34.917
YOU'RE RUBBING OFF
ON ME, MORGAN.

13:34.917 --> 13:38.125
BUT CHOPIN IS  PERFECT.

13:38.125 --> 13:41.834
SO THIS IS HOW YOU DO
WHAT YOU DO.

13:44.834 --> 13:49.667
THE TRUTH SPEAKS TO ME
FROM A PEACEFUL PLACE.

13:49.667 --> 13:52.375
I GOT TO SET THE STAGE
TO HEAR IT.

13:52.375 --> 13:53.834
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

13:53.834 --> 13:55.500
NO.

13:56.834 --> 13:59.500
I THRIVE ON CHAOS.

14:01.500 --> 14:05.333
[ MUSIC VOLUME INCREASES ]

14:05.333 --> 14:08.959
BUT THIS IS GOOD, TOO.

14:12.000 --> 14:15.834
[ JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING ]

14:21.917 --> 14:23.333
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

14:23.333 --> 14:26.500
I DIDN'T KILL HER.

14:26.500 --> 14:28.500
I WAS JUST TRYING
TO STOP THE BLOOD.

14:28.500 --> 14:29.625
JUST THE...

14:31.667 --> 14:33.125
NO FORCEFUL IMPACT SPATTER --

14:33.125 --> 14:36.500
HE'S TELLING THE TRUTH.
I CAN TELL.

14:36.500 --> 14:38.000
PALMS UP, PLEASE.

14:41.375 --> 14:42.625
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

14:42.625 --> 14:45.709
WHEN I FOUND BETSY,
SHE WAS STILL BREATHING.

14:45.709 --> 14:47.375
I WANTED TO HELP HER.

14:50.291 --> 14:51.917
YOU BELIEVE ME, RIGHT?

14:51.917 --> 14:54.875
I'M JUST THE LAB GUY,
MR. WILSON. SORRY.

14:56.542 --> 14:58.500
ARMS DOWN
AT YOUR SIDES, PLEASE.

15:01.875 --> 15:04.834
BLOOD MISTING. HUH.

15:08.625 --> 15:12.333
I NEED TO COLLECT HIS SHIRT
FOR EVIDENCE.

15:12.333 --> 15:14.083
UH...

15:17.291 --> 15:19.125
MORGAN!

15:22.917 --> 15:24.333
THE GIRL'S MOTHER
WAS AT WORK,

15:24.333 --> 15:26.208
BUT SHE ISN'T REALLY DEFENDING
HER HUSBAND.

15:26.208 --> 15:28.917
WILSON AND HIS STEPDAUGHTER
FOUGHT ALL THE TIME.

15:28.917 --> 15:31.291
THE NEIGHBORS HEARD HIM YELLING
AT HER THIS MORNING.

15:31.291 --> 15:33.792
THEN HE COMES HOME FOR LUNCH --
MOTIVE AND OPPORTUNITY.

15:33.792 --> 15:35.250
WHAT'D THE BLOOD SAY?

15:35.250 --> 15:37.291
WELL, THE BLOOD ON HIS HANDS
COULD HAVE COME

15:37.291 --> 15:39.875
FROM TRYING TO HELP HER,
LIKE HE CLAIMS.

15:42.000 --> 15:45.834
BUT I DID DETECT, UH, BLOOD MIST
ON HIS SHIRT.

15:45.834 --> 15:47.208
A BLOOD MIST --

15:47.208 --> 15:50.208
THE KIND THAT COMES FROM BEATING
ON A TEENAGE GIRL?

15:50.208 --> 15:52.333
NO.
YES.

15:52.333 --> 15:54.417
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY SURE?

15:54.417 --> 15:56.166
IT'S TOO FINE
FOR A BLUDGEONING.

15:56.166 --> 15:57.959
THE MIST IS FROM
A BLUDGEONING.

15:57.959 --> 16:01.291
MEDIUM-VELOCITY IMPACT
SPATTERS -- NO DOUBT ABOUT IT.

16:01.291 --> 16:03.500
OKAY, MORGAN.

16:03.500 --> 16:05.458
JUST MAKE SURE YOU GET ME
YOUR BLOOD REPORT

16:05.458 --> 16:06.750
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

16:13.291 --> 16:16.208
THIS IS MY CHANCE
TO MAKE DOAKES GO AWAY

16:16.208 --> 16:19.291
WITHOUT SPILLING A SINGLE DROP
OF HIS BLOOD.

16:19.291 --> 16:23.333
OF COURSE, I HAVE TO SELL
AN INNOCENT MAN DOWN THE RIVER.

16:23.333 --> 16:28.125
SORRY, MR. WILSON, BUT I WON'T
LET YOU FLOAT TOO FAR.

16:32.542 --> 16:34.917
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

16:36.792 --> 16:39.041
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT YOU.

16:39.041 --> 16:41.500
HMM.
I LIKE THE SOUND OF THAT.

16:41.500 --> 16:44.667
YEAH, I HAD TO DO A LITTLE
CREATIVE PROBLEM-SOLVING

16:44.667 --> 16:46.709
AT SOMEONE ELSE'S EXPENSE.

16:46.709 --> 16:48.083
BRAVO.

16:48.083 --> 16:50.000
Yeah,
I figured you'd like that.

16:50.000 --> 16:51.291
What's up?

16:51.291 --> 16:54.000
WELL, YOU KNOW
THAT ART INSTALLATION

16:54.000 --> 16:55.583
THAT I'VE BEEN WORKING ON?

16:55.583 --> 16:57.250
THE CANNIBALS.

16:57.250 --> 17:01.583
They're not cannibals.
How barbaric!

17:01.583 --> 17:03.000
THEIR EATING IS SYMBOLIC

17:03.000 --> 17:06.000
OF THE WAY WE CONSUME OTHERS
TO FEED OUR NEEDS.

17:06.000 --> 17:07.542
THAT'S WHAT I MEANT.

17:07.542 --> 17:10.500
WELL, IT SOLD.

17:10.500 --> 17:13.291
I-I DIDN'T EVEN CREATE IT
TO SELL, BUT ONE OF MY BUYERS

17:13.291 --> 17:16.000
fell in love with it,
and I named an outrageous price,

17:16.000 --> 17:18.875
and she paid me a deposit
on the spot.

17:18.875 --> 17:21.750
SO...

17:21.750 --> 17:24.166
YOU IN THE MOOD
TO CELEBRATE?

17:31.542 --> 17:34.917
DEFINITELY.

17:48.458 --> 17:50.583
I'M AFRAID WE JUST CAN'T
SEAT YOU TONIGHT

17:50.583 --> 17:51.959
WITHOUT A RESERVATION.

17:51.959 --> 17:54.417
AS YOU CAN SEE, WE ARE
COMPLETELY AT CAPACITY.

17:54.417 --> 17:55.709
OH, WELL --

17:55.709 --> 17:57.458
NO, I'M SORRY.
YOU HAVE TO HELP US.

17:57.458 --> 17:59.375
I MADE THIS RESERVATION
TWO MONTHS AGO.

17:59.375 --> 18:01.875
THIS IS OUR
10-YEAR ANNIVERSARY.

18:01.875 --> 18:05.166
THIS IS THE PLACE WHERE DEXTER
PROPOSED TO ME --

18:05.166 --> 18:08.709
ON THE PATIO,
IN FRONT OF THE FOUNTAIN.

18:10.250 --> 18:13.250
HE TOLD ME TO MAKE A WISH,
AND WHEN I LOOKED DOWN,

18:13.250 --> 18:18.667
THERE WAS MY DIAMOND RING,
SPARKLING UNDER THE WATER.

18:18.667 --> 18:21.125
THAT IS SO ROMANTIC.

18:21.125 --> 18:22.750
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:22.750 --> 18:24.583
Dexter:
IN CASE YOU'RE WONDERING,

18:24.583 --> 18:26.875
THERE'S NOTHING SPARKLING
UNDER THAT WATER TONIGHT.

18:26.875 --> 18:30.417
[ CHUCKLES ] OH, I'M SURE
YOU'LL DAZZLE ME SOMEHOW.

18:30.417 --> 18:33.792
YOU'RE A CREATIVE PROBLEM-SOLVER
NOW, RIGHT?

18:33.792 --> 18:37.625
A CHANGED MAN,
OR AT LEAST "CHANGING."

18:37.625 --> 18:39.083
I SUPPOSE.

18:39.083 --> 18:41.667
THERE'S NO SUPPOSING
ABOUT IT, DEXTER.

18:41.667 --> 18:44.166
YOU'VE TAKEN CONTROL
OF YOUR ADDICTION

18:44.166 --> 18:46.208
IN A WAY
THAT FEW PEOPLE DO.

18:46.208 --> 18:48.500
IT'S BEEN ABOUT A WEEK

18:48.500 --> 18:51.375
SINCE WE'VE EVEN DISCUSSED
YOUR RECOVERY.

18:51.375 --> 18:53.959
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

18:53.959 --> 18:56.959
AND YOU HAVEN'T FELT THE NEED
TO USE?

18:56.959 --> 18:59.792
INCREDIBLY, NO.
I FEEL...

18:59.792 --> 19:05.625
YOU KNOW, LIKE I'M FINALLY
IN CONTROL OF THINGS AGAIN.

19:05.625 --> 19:10.458
WE CALL THAT WARM FUZZY FEELING
THE PINK CLOUD.

19:10.458 --> 19:14.917
IT'S WHEN AN ADDICT EXPERIENCES
ACCEPTANCE FOR THE FIRST TIME.

19:14.917 --> 19:18.208
YOU'RE SAYING
IT WON'T LAST?

19:18.208 --> 19:22.625
I'M SAYING THAT YOU HAVE
TO WORK IT -- THAT'S ALL.

19:22.625 --> 19:25.750
BUT I KNOW THAT YOU WILL,

19:25.750 --> 19:28.834
BECAUSE I BELIEVE THAT
WE'VE FOUND A TRUE SUBSTITUTE

19:28.834 --> 19:30.667
FOR YOUR ADDICTION.

19:30.667 --> 19:32.834
WHAT'S THAT?

19:32.834 --> 19:36.208
LIFE.

19:44.583 --> 19:47.834
YOU'RE MAKING US ALL
LOOK BAD.

19:47.834 --> 19:49.667
I'M THE MANAGER
OF IL BISTRO VINO.

19:49.667 --> 19:51.458
HAPPY ANNIVERSARY --
ON THE HOUSE.

19:51.458 --> 19:53.583
THANK YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:53.583 --> 19:55.792
OH, DID YOU HEAR THAT,
DARLING?

19:55.792 --> 19:57.834
OH, I HEARD IT,
DARLING.

19:57.834 --> 19:59.834
ENJOY YOUR EVENING.

19:59.834 --> 20:02.333
THANK YOU.

20:02.333 --> 20:04.875
HAPPY ANNIVERSARY,
MY LOVE.

20:04.875 --> 20:06.333
AREN'T WE IN RECOVERY?

20:06.333 --> 20:08.041
OH, THIS?
IT'S JUST BUBBLES.

20:08.041 --> 20:09.834
WE'RE NOT GONNA SHOOT IT UP,
ARE WE?

20:09.834 --> 20:11.875
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:11.875 --> 20:13.792
YOU REALLY HAVE A WAY.
YOU KNOW THAT?

20:13.792 --> 20:15.125
A WAY OF WHAT?

20:15.125 --> 20:17.750
OF WHATEVER THE HELL
YOU WANT.

20:17.750 --> 20:21.000
WELL, HERE'S TO 10 MORE
GLORIOUS YEARS

20:21.000 --> 20:23.458
OF WHATEVER THE HELL I WANT.

20:23.458 --> 20:25.250
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

20:29.875 --> 20:33.959
HI, I'M CODY,
AND I RESEARCHED SAUDI ARABIA

20:33.959 --> 20:35.375
FOR MY CULTURAL REPORT.

20:35.375 --> 20:36.709
Gail:
THAT'S GOOD, SWEETIE.

20:36.709 --> 20:38.834
NOW, LOOK AT ME
WHEN YOU TALK, OKAY?

20:38.834 --> 20:40.542
AND TRY AND STAND UP
STRAIGHT.

20:40.542 --> 20:43.792
MY BOARD IS COVERED IN SAND

20:43.792 --> 20:47.291
BECAUSE SAUDI ARABIA
IS ONE BIG DESERT.

20:47.291 --> 20:49.000
ONE GREAT  BIG DESERT.

20:49.000 --> 20:50.792
ONE GREAT  BIG DESERT.

20:50.792 --> 20:54.500
IT ONLY RAINS IN A TINY CORNER
OF THE COUNTRY,

20:54.500 --> 20:55.792
SO THEY SAVE RAINWATER --

20:55.792 --> 20:58.917
OKAY, NOW, TRY AND KEEP
YOUR FINGERS OFF YOUR FACE.

20:58.917 --> 21:01.291
YOU DON'T WANT PEOPLE TO THINK
YOU'RE PICKING YOUR NOSE.

21:01.291 --> 21:03.750
YOU MEAN LIKE THIS?

21:03.750 --> 21:05.041
[ GIGGLES ]

21:05.041 --> 21:08.083
CODY, YOU NEED
TO TAKE THIS SERIOUSLY.

21:08.083 --> 21:11.166
DEXTER SAID IT SHOULD BE FUN.

21:11.166 --> 21:14.583
DEXTER DOES DRUGS.
HE'S WRONG.

21:14.583 --> 21:16.250
I FINISHED MY HOMEWORK.

21:16.250 --> 21:18.041
FOR THE WEEK?

21:21.000 --> 21:22.625
HEY, GUYS. I'M HOME.

21:22.625 --> 21:23.917
MOM!
SORRY I'M SO LATE.

21:23.917 --> 21:25.500
I'M SO HAPPY TO SEE YOU!

21:25.500 --> 21:27.291
MOM!

21:27.291 --> 21:29.417
OH, WOW!
WHAT A GREETING.

21:29.417 --> 21:32.250
OKAY, WHY DON'T YOU GUYS
GO GET READY FOR BED?

21:32.250 --> 21:34.208
REALLY, MOM?
I JUST GOT HOME.

21:34.208 --> 21:35.333
THEY NEED THEIR REST.

21:35.333 --> 21:38.792
I WILL BE IN IN JUST A MINUTE
TO CHECK ON YOU.

21:41.500 --> 21:44.500
THOSE TWO ARE MAKING
GREAT PROGRESS.

21:44.500 --> 21:46.458
PROGRESS -- TOWARDS WHAT?

21:46.458 --> 21:47.625
THEIR FULL POTENTIAL!

21:47.625 --> 21:49.291
[ SIGHS ]

21:52.709 --> 21:54.917
MOM, I KNOW YOU'RE REALLY GOOD
AT THESE THINGS,

21:54.917 --> 21:56.166
BUT NOW THAT YOU'RE HERE,

21:56.166 --> 21:58.125
HAVE YOU THOUGHT ABOUT APPLYING
FOR A TEACHING JOB?

21:58.125 --> 22:01.458
NO, I'M THROUGH
WITH THE SCHOOLS.

22:01.458 --> 22:04.083
WELL, I THOUGHT TEACHING
WAS YOUR LIFE.

22:04.083 --> 22:07.250
AND YOUR CHILDREN ARE GOING
TO BE THE BENEFICIARIES

22:07.250 --> 22:08.750
OF ALL THAT I HAVE
TO OFFER.

22:10.625 --> 22:12.709
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

22:12.709 --> 22:14.583
OUR INJUNCTION
STOPPED THE TRIBUNE

22:14.583 --> 22:18.000
FROM PUBLISHING
THE MANIFESTO -- FOR NOW.

22:18.000 --> 22:19.125
AT THE VERY LEAST,

22:19.125 --> 22:20.959
WE'LL HAVE TIME
TO GET A JUMP ON THINGS

22:20.959 --> 22:22.709
BEFORE THE NEWS FRENZY HITS.

22:22.709 --> 22:26.125
SO, LET'S TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THIS WINDOW.

22:26.125 --> 22:29.375
OUR GOAL FOR THE NEXT 48 HOURS
IS TO WADE THROUGH

22:29.375 --> 22:31.834
THIS SHINING PIECE
OF SOCIAL COMMENTARY.

22:31.834 --> 22:35.166
I'VE NEVER SEEN SO MANY DENSE
AND CONVOLUTED IDEAS IN MY LIFE,

22:35.166 --> 22:38.792
BUT WE NEED TO SEARCH THEM ALL
FOR CLUES TO HIS IDENTITY.

22:38.792 --> 22:41.750
SO, FIRST IMPRESSIONS?
I GOT SOMETHING.

22:41.750 --> 22:45.166
THERE ARE A LOT OF LITERARY
REFERENCES IN THIS DOCUMENT.

22:45.166 --> 22:46.834
HOW DO YOU KNOW?
I LIKE TO READ BOOKS.

22:46.834 --> 22:48.041
WHAT KIND OF BOOKS?

22:48.041 --> 22:49.834
ALL KINDS. WHO CARES?

22:49.834 --> 22:55.208
ANYWAY...I SEE LOTS OF
REFERENCES, LIKE THIS ONE.

22:55.208 --> 22:58.417
"YOU CAN'T DEPEND
ON YOUR EYES

22:58.417 --> 23:00.834
WHEN YOUR IMAGINATION
IS OUT OF FOCUS."

23:00.834 --> 23:03.542
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE'S A TREKKER!

23:03.542 --> 23:06.041
THAT SHIT'S STRAIGHT
FROM "DEEP SPACE NINE."

23:06.041 --> 23:08.291
WHAT?
MARK TWAIN SAID THAT.

23:08.291 --> 23:10.458
IT'S ONE OF
HIS MOST FAMOUS QUOTES.

23:10.458 --> 23:13.208
TWAIN WAS NEVER
ON "DEEP SPACE NINE."

23:13.208 --> 23:14.375
HE WAS ON "NEXT GENERATION."

23:14.375 --> 23:15.959
HE DIDN'T SAY IT
ON "STAR TREK."

23:15.959 --> 23:17.000
OKAY, SO WHAT'S IT FROM?

23:17.000 --> 23:20.208
"A CONNECTICUT YANKEE
IN KING ARTHUR'S COURT."

23:20.208 --> 23:26.583
ANGEL, WHAT OTHER LITERARY
QUOTES ARE IN THAT MANIFESTO?

23:26.583 --> 23:30.834
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

23:30.834 --> 23:36.583
THIS GUY -- HE'S THE BEST BOXING
STUDENT I HAVE EVER HAD.

23:36.583 --> 23:39.333
AFTER FOUR WEEKS, HE'S GETTING
IN SHOTS TO MY HEAD.

23:39.333 --> 23:41.750
AND FINALLY HE SAYS,
"I THINK I'M READY."

23:41.750 --> 23:44.250
I'M LIKE,
"YOU'RE READY FOR WHAT?"

23:44.250 --> 23:48.458
AND HE SAYS,
"TO KICK MY MOM'S ASS."

23:48.458 --> 23:50.458
I'M LIKE,
"YOU'RE LEARNING HOW TO BOX

23:50.458 --> 23:52.667
BECAUSE YOU WANT TO BEAT UP
YOUR MOM?"

23:52.667 --> 23:56.917
[ CHOPIN'S "NOCTURNE NUMBER 2
IN E FLAT MAJOR" PLAYING ]

23:56.917 --> 23:58.709
[ VOICE FADING ]

23:58.709 --> 24:01.792
[ CHOPIN'S "NOCTURNE NUMBER 2
IN E FLAT MAJOR" CONTINUES ]

24:18.500 --> 24:19.875
[ DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

24:19.875 --> 24:22.250
WHAT THE FUCK?!

24:22.250 --> 24:23.583
DID -- DID YOU HEAR
WHAT I SAID?

24:23.583 --> 24:24.709
I WAS GONNA HIT THE SHOWERS.

24:24.709 --> 24:26.291
I'LL MEET YOU BACK HERE
IN 10 MINUTES.

24:26.291 --> 24:28.583
OKAY, YEAH, 10 MINUTES.

24:47.875 --> 24:49.583
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:51.291 --> 24:54.083
WHO THE FUCK ARE YOU?

24:55.709 --> 24:59.125
OH, HI! I'M LILA.

24:59.125 --> 25:01.166
OH, PARDON MY TITS.

25:01.166 --> 25:04.834
UM, WE THOUGHT YOU WERE CRASHING
AT YOUR BOYFRIEND'S TONIGHT.

25:04.834 --> 25:06.583
WE -- WE WHO?

25:06.583 --> 25:09.000
DEXTER AND I.

25:09.000 --> 25:13.458
COULD YOU JUST...WAIT HERE
A MINUTE?

25:18.041 --> 25:20.500
WHO'S THE SKANK?

25:20.500 --> 25:22.709
DEB, DID KNOCKING OCCUR
TO YOU?

25:22.709 --> 25:24.291
WHO IS SHE?

25:24.291 --> 25:26.542
AND ARE YOU TRYING TO FUCK HER
OR SET HER ON FIRE?

25:26.542 --> 25:27.792
[ SIGHS ]

25:27.792 --> 25:30.208
I DIDN'T DO THIS TO YOU WHEN YOU
WERE RIDING SQUARE-JAW GUY

25:30.208 --> 25:31.333
WITH THE HANDCUFFS.

25:31.333 --> 25:32.500
THAT'S DIFFERENT.

25:32.500 --> 25:35.458
I WASN'T CHEATING ON ANYONE
WITH GABRIEL.

25:35.458 --> 25:38.166
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS TO RITA,
NOT TO MENTION HER KIDS?

25:38.166 --> 25:39.583
YOU'RE LIKE THEIR FATHER.

25:39.583 --> 25:41.625
HEY, RITA BROKE UP
WITH ME,  OKAY?

25:41.625 --> 25:44.667
YOU FUCKED UP, DEX...

25:46.125 --> 25:48.166
...BIG-TIME.

25:48.166 --> 25:50.750
EW. EXCUSE ME.

25:53.375 --> 25:54.667
[ SIGHS ]

26:05.041 --> 26:07.709
DON'T WORRY.

26:07.709 --> 26:10.333
SHE JUST NEEDS SOME TIME
TO ADJUST -- THAT'S ALL.

26:15.417 --> 26:17.875
I HAD OFFICERS TEAR APART
THE STEPFATHER'S HOUSE --

26:17.875 --> 26:20.583
NO MURDER WEAPON, BUT HE HAD
TO HIDE IT SOMEWHERE.

26:20.583 --> 26:22.417
WHERE IS WILSON NOW?
INTERVIEW ROOM 2.

26:22.417 --> 26:26.583
WE STILL HAVE HIM?
WHY DIDN'T HIS LAWYER POST BOND?

26:26.583 --> 26:29.125
WELL, HE TRIED, BUT I PULLED IN
A FAVOR AT THE COURTHOUSE

26:29.125 --> 26:30.291
AND GOT A BAIL ENHANCEMENT,

26:30.291 --> 26:32.250
SO THEY HAD TO START
THE PAPERWORK ALL OVER AGAIN.

26:32.250 --> 26:34.458
I'M GONNA BREAK
THAT COCKSUCKER TODAY.

26:34.458 --> 26:37.750
WHAT EVIDENCE YOU SAY
WE GOT ON THIS GUY?

26:37.750 --> 26:39.625
HE WAS DRIPPING
IN THE VICTIM'S BLOOD.

26:39.625 --> 26:41.083
HE WAS HOME ALONE WITH HER.

26:41.083 --> 26:43.750
THEY FOUGHT THE MORNING
OF THE MURDER.
ALL CIRCUMSTANTIAL.

26:43.750 --> 26:46.083
YEAH, BUT THE BLOOD SPATTER
ON HIS SHIRT WAS A DIRECT RESULT

26:46.083 --> 26:47.458
OF A BLUNT-FORCE
BEATING, MARIA.

26:47.458 --> 26:50.500
I'D LIKE TO SEE
THE BLOOD REPORT.

26:50.500 --> 26:52.333
YOU'LL GET IT
AS SOON AS I DO.

26:52.333 --> 26:55.625
IF YOU'RE LOOKING FOR ME,
I'LL BE QUESTIONING THE SUSPECT.

27:00.709 --> 27:02.583
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

27:12.458 --> 27:15.750
THEY'RE STILL PLAYING MY TUNE.

27:18.125 --> 27:21.208
IT'S LIKE I'M CONDUCTING
A FINAL SYMPHONY,

27:21.208 --> 27:23.750
"REQUIEM FOR DEMONIC DEXTER."

27:29.834 --> 27:32.333
AND FORMING THE ENTIRE
BRASS SECTION,

27:32.333 --> 27:35.083
SERGEANT JAMES DOAKES.

27:35.083 --> 27:36.542
WHEN I REACH THE END,

27:36.542 --> 27:38.291
MAYBE I CAN LAY TO REST
THE MONSTER

27:38.291 --> 27:40.333
FORMERLY KNOWN AS DEXTER.

27:40.333 --> 27:45.417
JUST HANG IN THERE, MR. WILSON.

27:58.959 --> 28:01.625
I'VE ASKED A PSYCHOLINGUIST
AT M.I.T.

28:01.625 --> 28:03.583
TO ANALYZE OUR MANIFESTO.

28:03.583 --> 28:07.041
HIS COMPUTER TABULATES
PUNCTUATION, MISSPELLINGS,

28:07.041 --> 28:09.834
AND SENTENCE STRUCTURE
TO IDENTIFY A SET OF KEY WORDS,

28:09.834 --> 28:12.959
WHICH HE'LL USE TO CREATE
A PROFILE OF OUR KILLER.

28:12.959 --> 28:17.166
SOUNDS...COMPLICATED.
STAY ON IT.

28:17.166 --> 28:20.208
OKAY, WE'VE BEEN AT THIS
TOO LONG.

28:20.208 --> 28:22.542
IT'S, UH, 1:00.

28:22.542 --> 28:23.875
LET'S BREAK FOR LUNCH.

28:34.417 --> 28:36.291
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

28:36.291 --> 28:38.166
HUH? YEAH, I'M FINE.

28:39.709 --> 28:41.125
ANYTHING YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT?

28:41.125 --> 28:44.542
NO, NOT REALLY.

28:44.542 --> 28:46.792
WELL,
IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND --
IT'S MY BROTHER.

28:46.792 --> 28:48.709
HE WAS DATING THIS CHICK --

28:48.709 --> 28:51.667
SUPERSWEET,
A LITTLE DOE-EYED.

28:51.667 --> 28:53.542
BUT, GOD, FOR HIM,
FUCKING PERFECT,

28:53.542 --> 28:55.041
AND HE JUST THREW HER AWAY.

28:55.041 --> 28:57.709
I'M JUST PISSED AT DEXTER,
NOT TO MENTION MY BOYFRIEND,

28:57.709 --> 28:59.792
WHO DID ABSOLUTELY
NOTHING WRONG.

28:59.792 --> 29:02.208
BUT EVERY TIME HE OPENED
HIS MOUTH LAST NIGHT,

29:02.208 --> 29:03.959
I WANTED TO FUCKING
SLAP HIM.

29:03.959 --> 29:05.583
YOU'VE BEEN LISTENING
TO CHOPIN.

29:05.583 --> 29:07.917
YEAH,
I DOWNLOADED A CHOPIN --

29:07.917 --> 29:11.500
UM, "NOCTURNE NUMBER 2
IN E FLAT MAJOR."

29:11.500 --> 29:12.792
ONE OF MY FAVORITES.

29:12.792 --> 29:16.417
IT, UH, CAN HAVE THIS EFFECT
ON PEOPLE.

29:16.417 --> 29:18.875
IT CAN STIR UP SOME DUST.

29:18.875 --> 29:21.208
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO SHIT.

29:26.375 --> 29:28.083
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:28.083 --> 29:32.583
LISTEN, YOU --
YOU CAN HEAL YOURSELF, SIR.

29:32.583 --> 29:34.667
JUST -- YOU JUST NEED
TO TALK TO ME.

29:34.667 --> 29:36.166
GET IT OFF YOU,

29:36.166 --> 29:38.500
OTHERWISE, IT'S GONNA HAUNT YOU
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

29:38.500 --> 29:40.291
[ Crying  ]  WHY DON'T YOU
JUST LISTEN TO ME?

29:40.291 --> 29:41.792
I DIDN'T DO THIS.

29:41.792 --> 29:45.583
YOU -- YOU CAN'T SAY IT
AND MAKE IT TRUE.

29:45.583 --> 29:47.208
YOU HAVE A CONSCIENCE,

29:47.208 --> 29:50.208
AND IT'S REALLY FUCKING
WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

29:50.208 --> 29:52.250
I WISH IT WERE ME.
I WISH I WERE DEAD.

29:52.250 --> 29:53.750
YEAH.

29:53.750 --> 29:55.750
WHY ARE WE QUESTIONING
THAT GUY?

29:55.750 --> 29:57.458
HE'S A MURDER SUSPECT.

29:57.458 --> 29:59.208
NO, HE'S NOT.
HE'S INNOCENT.

29:59.208 --> 30:02.291
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

30:02.291 --> 30:03.875
MY BLOOD REPORT
BACKED HIS STORY.

30:03.875 --> 30:05.542
MR. WILSON FOUND
HIS STEPDAUGHTER DEAD,

30:05.542 --> 30:07.792
JUST LIKE I TOLD SERGEANT DOAKES
AT THE CRIME SCENE.

30:07.792 --> 30:10.417
YOU TURNED IN THE BLOOD REPORT?
WHEN?

30:10.417 --> 30:11.959
I DON'T KNOW --

30:11.959 --> 30:13.750
AT SOME POINT
BEFORE I WENT HOME LAST NIGHT.

30:13.750 --> 30:15.333
I PUT IT RIGHT
ON THE SERGEANT'S DESK,

30:15.333 --> 30:17.458
JUST LIKE HE ASKED.

30:17.458 --> 30:18.750
THE GREEN FOLDER.

30:22.500 --> 30:24.250
YEAH,
ACCORDING TO MY FINDINGS,

30:24.250 --> 30:26.625
THE MIST ON THE STEPFATHER'S
SHIRT WAS EXHALED

30:26.625 --> 30:28.792
FROM THE VICTIM WHEN HE TRIED
TO REVIVE HER.

30:28.792 --> 30:30.917
THE AUTOPSY CONFIRMED SHE HAD
SEVERE INTERNAL BLEEDING,

30:30.917 --> 30:32.792
DUE TO THE BLUDGEONING.

30:32.792 --> 30:35.458
YEAH, BUT HE COULD HAVE
BEATEN HER FIRST.

30:35.458 --> 30:36.875
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

30:36.875 --> 30:41.125
THE CRIME-SCENE PHOTOS SHOW
BLOOD RADIATING OUTWARD

30:41.125 --> 30:42.500
AROUND THE VICTIM'S BODY.

30:42.500 --> 30:44.875
THAT KIND OF BLUDGEONING WOULD
HAVE COVERED THE REAL KILLER

30:44.875 --> 30:47.333
IN BLOOD FROM HEAD TO TOE.

30:47.333 --> 30:49.625
THANKS.

30:53.792 --> 30:56.000
MR. WILSON,
YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

30:56.000 --> 30:58.125
WHAT THE HELL? LIEUTENANT,
THIS MAN IS A KILLER.

30:58.125 --> 31:00.834
THIS MAN HAS BEEN THROUGH ENOUGH
FOR ONE DAY.

31:00.834 --> 31:04.000
THERE'S AN OFFICER
IN THE HALLWAY.

31:04.000 --> 31:05.959
HE'LL SEE THAT YOU GET
YOUR PERSONAL BELONGINGS BACK

31:05.959 --> 31:07.083
AND TAKE YOU HOME.

31:07.083 --> 31:09.959
THANK YOU, MA'AM.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

31:18.125 --> 31:19.667
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

31:19.667 --> 31:21.750
TRYING TO SAVE YOUR CAREER,
JAMES, IF IT ISN'T TOO LATE.

31:21.750 --> 31:23.792
DID YOU EVEN CHECK
THE BLOOD REPORT?

31:23.792 --> 31:25.375
I DIDN'T GET
THE BLOOD REPORT.

31:25.375 --> 31:28.834
IT'S ON YOUR DESK,
AND IT EXONERATES YOUR SUSPECT.

31:28.834 --> 31:30.792
WE SHOULD BE OUT THERE
LOOKING FOR THE REAL  KILLER.

31:30.792 --> 31:33.000
MARIA, THAT IS NOT
WHAT HE TOLD ME AT --

31:33.000 --> 31:36.542
THAT MOTHERFUCKER.

31:36.542 --> 31:38.959
[ SCOFFS ] HE'S GOOD.

31:38.959 --> 31:40.333
WHO?

31:40.333 --> 31:41.750
MORGAN.

31:41.750 --> 31:44.291
HE PLANNED THIS WHOLE THING.

31:44.291 --> 31:46.166
MARIA,
THAT PSYCHOPATH SET ME UP.

31:46.166 --> 31:48.917
DEXTER AGAIN?
YOU'RE BLAMING DEXTER FOR THIS?

31:48.917 --> 31:51.625
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW PATHETIC THAT SOUNDS?

31:51.625 --> 31:53.083
THIS IS NOT ABOUT DEXTER!

31:53.083 --> 31:56.208
THIS IS ABOUT THE POOR JUDGMENT
YOU HAVE BEEN DISPLAYING

31:56.208 --> 31:58.208
IN THIS DEPARTMENT
FOR MONTHS NOW!

31:58.208 --> 32:01.458
[ CHOPIN'S "NOCTURNE NUMBER 2
IN E FLAT MAJOR" PLAYING ]

32:01.458 --> 32:03.500
YOU WANT TO WORK OUT?

32:03.500 --> 32:04.542
NO.

32:06.792 --> 32:10.250
I WASN'T TALKING
ABOUT THE GYM.

32:10.250 --> 32:11.125
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:12.875 --> 32:16.125
YOU'RE SWEET,
BUT I'M REALLY NOT IN THE MOOD.

32:18.542 --> 32:19.542
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT TO DO?

32:24.875 --> 32:26.125
UH...

32:28.250 --> 32:30.750
I THINK I WANT TO BREAK UP.

32:34.375 --> 32:36.125
FOR REAL?

32:36.125 --> 32:38.500
YEAH.

32:38.500 --> 32:40.583
IS THAT OKAY?

32:40.583 --> 32:44.041
[ SCOFFS ]

32:44.041 --> 32:46.417
NO.

32:46.417 --> 32:48.166
NO, IT'S NOT OKAY.

32:48.166 --> 32:49.750
FUCK, WHAT DID I DO, DEB?

32:49.750 --> 32:51.917
NOTHING.
I SWEAR TO GOD.

32:51.917 --> 32:56.792
YOU'RE...SMOKING HOT
AND...FUN

32:56.792 --> 33:00.625
AND...SOULFUL AND...

33:00.625 --> 33:02.500
AGE-APPROPRIATE.

33:02.500 --> 33:03.667
AND BUT WHAT?

33:03.667 --> 33:05.291
BUT...

33:05.291 --> 33:10.500
SOMETIMES THE TRUTH SPEAKS
FROM A PEACEFUL PLACE.

33:10.500 --> 33:13.125
IT'S TAKEN ME A LONG TIME
TO FIND THAT PLACE,

33:13.125 --> 33:15.083
BUT I THINK I HAVE,

33:15.083 --> 33:18.500
AND IT'S TELLING ME YOU'RE NOT
THE RIGHT ONE FOR ME.

33:25.417 --> 33:27.667
I'M SO SORRY.

33:33.583 --> 33:36.500
YOU LIVE IN A NICE
NEIGHBORHOOD.

33:36.500 --> 33:38.542
YEAH, I HAD NO IDEA.

33:38.542 --> 33:41.667
I'M USUALLY PASSING BY
AT 35 MILES PER HOUR.

33:41.667 --> 33:43.500
I'M NOT A REAL BIG WALKER.

33:43.500 --> 33:47.458
[ CHUCKLES ]
EVERYBODY WALKS IN LONDON.

33:47.458 --> 33:51.000
OF COURSE, THEY'RE USUALLY
WALKING TO THE PUB.

33:51.000 --> 33:52.667
HOW FAR ARE WE  GOING?

33:54.583 --> 33:58.417
OH, YOU'RE A BIT GRUMPY
TONIGHT.

33:58.417 --> 33:59.875
WHAT'S WRONG?

33:59.875 --> 34:01.667
[ SIGHS ]

34:04.500 --> 34:08.625
COME ON.
DON'T CLOSE UP ON ME NOW.

34:08.625 --> 34:10.041
NO,
I HONESTLY DON'T KNOW.

34:10.041 --> 34:12.667
I MEAN, THANKS TO YOU,
THINGS ARE...

34:12.667 --> 34:14.250
ACTUALLY LOOKING UP.

34:14.250 --> 34:17.375
SOME PEOPLE AT WORK
HAVE BEEN...AFTER ME.

34:17.375 --> 34:20.208
I THINK I HAVE 'EM
UNDER CONTROL.

34:20.208 --> 34:25.166
SO, WHY THE GROUCHINESS?

34:27.041 --> 34:30.041
IS IT BECAUSE YOUR SISTER THINKS
I'M A TROLLOP?

34:30.041 --> 34:33.834
IT'S NOT JUST...DEB.

34:33.834 --> 34:37.959
IT'S THE SUDDENNESS
OF ALL OF THIS --

34:37.959 --> 34:41.041
LOSING RITA, THE KIDS.

34:41.041 --> 34:45.500
THEY'VE BEEN THE ONLY THING
KEEPING ME HUMAN

34:45.500 --> 34:48.709
FOR A LONG TIME.

34:52.250 --> 34:55.208
WERE  THEY KEEPING YOU HUMAN,
THOUGH,

34:55.208 --> 34:58.458
OR WERE THEY THE ONES MAKING
YOU FEEL LIKE THE MONSTER

34:58.458 --> 35:00.208
THAT YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT?

35:04.917 --> 35:06.625
KEEP GOING.

35:06.625 --> 35:09.834
YOUR FRIENDS AND FAMILY
HAVE TO ACCEPT YOU

35:09.834 --> 35:13.542
FOR WHO YOU'RE EVOLVING INTO
NOW THAT YOU'RE CLEAN.

35:13.542 --> 35:17.333
IS THAT WHAT I AM --

35:17.333 --> 35:19.291
CLEAN?

35:21.917 --> 35:24.792
'CAUSE I DON'T FEEL THAT WAY
AT ALL.

35:26.834 --> 35:30.083
NO, YOU CERTAINLY DON'T.

35:30.083 --> 35:33.458
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:33.458 --> 35:36.625
MMM, GOD.

35:36.625 --> 35:40.083
I WISH I COULD FUCK YOU
RIGHT NOW.

35:49.583 --> 35:50.959
WHOSE HOUSE IS THIS?

35:50.959 --> 35:52.041
COULDN'T TELL YOU.

35:52.041 --> 35:53.458
GOD.

35:53.458 --> 35:54.458
[ GASPS ]

35:54.458 --> 35:56.333
HE'S A MAN OF MANY TALENTS.

36:03.291 --> 36:05.166
AH!

36:14.083 --> 36:16.208
[ LAUGHS ]

36:19.083 --> 36:22.208
[ MOANING ]

36:25.375 --> 36:28.709
LOOK.
I'M SOME OLD BITCH.

36:28.709 --> 36:31.875
BETTER NOT PRESS OUR LUCK.
WE SHOULD GO.

36:31.875 --> 36:33.667
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

36:33.667 --> 36:36.250
[ SIGHS ]

36:36.250 --> 36:38.166
HELLO?

36:38.166 --> 36:40.333
Cody: Hi, Dexter.

36:40.333 --> 36:42.000
CODY?

36:42.000 --> 36:45.917
CAN YOU COME
TO MY SCHOOL TOMORROW?

36:45.917 --> 36:48.250
WHAT'S AT YOUR SCHOOL,
BUDDY?

36:48.250 --> 36:50.542
I'm doing
my cultural report.

36:50.542 --> 36:52.375
[ SIGHS ]

36:52.375 --> 36:55.041
SAUDI ARABIA.

36:55.041 --> 36:57.959
CAN YOU WATCH ME?
I'M KIND OF SCARED.

36:57.959 --> 37:00.000
Gail: Cody,
what are you doing?

37:03.083 --> 37:04.667
WHO IS THIS?

37:04.667 --> 37:06.834
DEXTER.

37:09.583 --> 37:11.250
[ TELEPHONE BEEPS ]

37:11.250 --> 37:13.333
HELLO?

37:16.208 --> 37:18.208
WHO WAS THAT?

37:19.875 --> 37:21.709
RITA'S SON.

37:21.709 --> 37:25.709
HE WANTS ME TO COME SEE HIM
AT SCHOOL TOMORROW.

37:25.709 --> 37:28.000
OH, POOR KID.

37:28.000 --> 37:31.083
HE DOESN'T UNDERSTAND
THAT YOU'VE GONE.

37:33.583 --> 37:35.250
I THINK I'LL GO.

37:41.000 --> 37:43.542
WHATEVER YOU THINK'S BEST.

37:52.583 --> 37:54.709
HEY, GUYS!

37:54.709 --> 37:57.250
I'M HOME!

37:59.667 --> 38:01.333
HELLO?

38:01.333 --> 38:02.542
THEY'RE IN BED.

38:02.542 --> 38:04.583
WHY SO EARLY?

38:04.583 --> 38:07.083
CODY IS BEING PUNISHED
FOR SNEAKING AWAY

38:07.083 --> 38:09.500
TO MAKE A PHONE CALL
WITHOUT PERMISSION.

38:09.500 --> 38:12.250
ASTOR JOINED HIM IN A MISGUIDED
SHOW OF SUPPORT.

38:12.250 --> 38:14.792
WELL, WHO WAS CODY CALLING?

38:14.792 --> 38:16.125
DEXTER.

38:16.125 --> 38:18.959
THE BOY WAS TRYING
TO INVITE HIM TO HIS SCHOOL.

38:18.959 --> 38:20.625
CAN YOU IMAGINE?
OH.

38:22.250 --> 38:24.375
MOM, WE NEED TO HAVE A TALK.

38:24.375 --> 38:26.750
I MADE A PHONE CALL
OF MY OWN TODAY.

38:26.750 --> 38:28.792
I SPOKE WITH AUNT CECILIA.

38:28.792 --> 38:33.417
SHE TOLD ME THE SCHOOL DISTRICT
FIRED YOU ALMOST A YEAR AGO.

38:36.500 --> 38:39.542
WE HAD PHILOSOPHICAL
DIFFERENCES.

38:39.542 --> 38:42.417
THE EDUCATIONAL SYSTEM
IS FALLING APART.

38:42.417 --> 38:46.083
SCHOOL SHOULD BE LIFE ITSELF,
NOT A PREPARATION FOR LIVING.

38:46.083 --> 38:49.375
DO YOU KNOW THAT THEY GIVE
TROPHIES TO EVERY CHILD NOW

38:49.375 --> 38:51.041
WHETHER THEY WIN OR LOSE?

38:51.041 --> 38:52.458
YEAH, I FINALLY GET IT.

38:52.458 --> 38:56.000
IT TOOK ME A FEW DECADES,
BUT IT'S NOT JUST ME --

38:56.000 --> 38:58.000
NOBODY CAN DEAL WITH YOU.

38:58.000 --> 39:01.250
YOU DON'T LEAVE ROOM
FOR ANYBODY ELSE TO EXIST.

39:01.250 --> 39:04.125
IT'S NOT MY FAULT THAT
SO MANY PEOPLE ARE WILLING

39:04.125 --> 39:05.750
TO SETTLE FOR MEDIOCRITY.

39:05.750 --> 39:09.166
JUST LOOK AT YOU --
FIRST PAUL, THEN DEXTER.

39:09.166 --> 39:11.667
RITA, YOU LACK
EVEN COMMON SENSE,

39:11.667 --> 39:15.333
AND NOW YOU'RE PASSING
THAT TORCH OF ORDINARY CHARACTER

39:15.333 --> 39:17.500
ON TO YOUR CHILDREN.

39:17.500 --> 39:19.000
SHUT THE FUCK UP.

39:21.208 --> 39:23.208
NOBODY TALKS ABOUT MY KIDS
THAT WAY.

39:23.208 --> 39:25.583
THATAGIRL.

39:25.583 --> 39:28.667
THAT'S  WHAT I'VE BEEN WAITING
TO SEE.

39:28.667 --> 39:30.583
YEAH!
I'M DONE WITH YOU.

39:30.583 --> 39:32.041
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

39:32.041 --> 39:34.750
BUT YOU GO --
YOU GIVE ME HELL.

39:34.750 --> 39:35.834
NO.

39:35.834 --> 39:38.041
NO, I WON'T  DO THAT.

39:38.041 --> 39:40.792
I WON'T LET YOU TURN ME
INTO...YOU.

39:40.792 --> 39:43.166
RITA --
HERE'S WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN --

39:43.166 --> 39:44.667
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING,

39:44.667 --> 39:46.500
YOU'RE GONNA PACK UP
AND GO HOME.

39:46.500 --> 39:49.500
YOU'LL COME AND VISIT US
FOR BIRTHDAYS AND HOLIDAYS,

39:49.500 --> 39:51.417
BUT YOU'RE NOT GONNA LIVE
WITH US ANYMORE.

39:54.208 --> 39:55.917
WELL...

39:57.709 --> 40:01.166
...IF THAT'S WHAT I HAVE
TO SACRIFICE

40:01.166 --> 40:03.417
TO GET YOU ON YOUR FEET...

40:15.875 --> 40:18.125
"KILL ONE MAN,
AND YOU'RE A MURDERER.

40:18.125 --> 40:19.625
"KILL THOUSANDS,
A CONQUEROR.

40:19.625 --> 40:21.709
KILL THEM ALL,
AND YOU'RE A GOD."

40:21.709 --> 40:23.375
DOES IT SOUND TO YOU
LIKE OUR GUY

40:23.375 --> 40:25.500
HAS A NARCISSISTIC
PERSONALITY DISORDER,

40:25.500 --> 40:27.417
A CLASSIC GOD COMPLEX?

40:27.417 --> 40:29.291
I THINK YOU'RE
ONTO SOMETHING, ANGEL.

40:29.291 --> 40:30.458
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,

40:30.458 --> 40:33.166
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
MY ALTER EGO HAD IN MIND

40:33.166 --> 40:34.500
WHEN HE WROTE THAT CRAP.

40:34.500 --> 40:36.917
I JUST PULLED FROM VARIOUS
BLOGS ON THE INTERNET,

40:36.917 --> 40:39.875
MIXED AND MATCHED --
PRESTO MANIFESTO.

40:45.583 --> 40:48.709
YOU FINALLY DECIDED
TO FIGHT BACK.

40:49.917 --> 40:52.917
I BEEN WAITING.

40:52.917 --> 40:55.917
HOPE YOU DON'T EXPECT ME
TO COMMENT ON THAT

40:55.917 --> 40:58.500
SO YOU CAN RECORD IT
ON YOUR HIDDEN TAPE RECORDER.

40:58.500 --> 40:59.917
I WASN'T BORN YESTERDAY.

40:59.917 --> 41:02.208
YOU MIGHT HAVE BEEN,
FOR ALL I KNOW.

41:02.208 --> 41:05.583
YOUR PAST IS A BIGGER MYSTERY
THAN FUCKING JIMMY HOFFA.

41:05.583 --> 41:09.375
I TRIED EVERY AVENUE,
LEGAL AND OTHERWISE,

41:09.375 --> 41:11.333
BUT THERE AIN'T NO
PAPER TRAIL

41:11.333 --> 41:14.375
ON THE EARLY YEARS
OF DEXTER MORGAN.

41:14.375 --> 41:18.000
I GUESS THERE'S NO RECORDER
RUNNING, AFTER ALL.

41:18.000 --> 41:21.125
[ CHUCKLES ] NO, MAN.

41:21.125 --> 41:23.458
UNLIKE YOU, I DO EVERYTHING
OUT IN THE OPEN.

41:23.458 --> 41:26.625
[ SIGHS ]

41:26.625 --> 41:28.458
WELL, IN THAT CASE,
SERGEANT,

41:28.458 --> 41:30.458
LET ME PUT THIS IN THE OPEN
FOR YOU.

41:31.875 --> 41:34.709
NO MATTER WHAT YOU TRY,
NO MATTER WHEN,

41:34.709 --> 41:36.792
NO MATTER HOW HARD YOU WORK,

41:36.792 --> 41:40.667
I'LL ALWAYS BE A STEP AHEAD
OF YOU FOR ONE SIMPLE REASON.

41:40.667 --> 41:43.625
AND WHAT'S THAT?

41:43.625 --> 41:45.500
I OWN YOU.

41:45.500 --> 41:47.125
AAH!

41:47.125 --> 41:50.291
AAH! FUCK!

42:03.500 --> 42:05.959
GET HIM OFF OF ME!
GET OFF ME!

42:08.000 --> 42:10.583
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?!

42:10.583 --> 42:11.959
STOP!

42:19.000 --> 42:23.667
I WANT YOUR GUN, YOUR BADGE,
AND YOUR POLICE I.D.

42:23.667 --> 42:25.959
I WANT YOUR
ACCESS CARD, TOO --

42:25.959 --> 42:27.500
NOW!

42:27.500 --> 42:29.875
TYPE A STATEMENT
THAT SERGEANT DOAKES

42:29.875 --> 42:31.709
IS ON ADMINISTRATIVE LEAVE,

42:31.709 --> 42:35.000
PENDING AN INTERNAL AFFAIRS
INVESTIGATION.

42:37.375 --> 42:39.166
YOU TWO,
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

42:40.959 --> 42:42.166
THANKS.

42:51.834 --> 42:53.542
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

42:53.542 --> 42:57.333
I DON'T KNOW.
HE JUST...JUMPED ME.

42:57.333 --> 42:59.000
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

43:00.750 --> 43:03.750
THAT GUY'S ALWAYS
HAD IT OUT FOR ME.

43:03.750 --> 43:06.125
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

43:13.667 --> 43:15.583
Lundy: THANKS FOR MEETING
WITH ME, DON.

43:15.583 --> 43:17.834
Don: WELL, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THE POINT IS.

43:17.834 --> 43:20.667
THE DISTRICT COURT INJUNCTION
HEARING STARTS IN THREE HOURS.

43:20.667 --> 43:23.458
WHICH EVERYONE HERE KNOWS
WE'RE GOING TO LOSE.

43:23.458 --> 43:26.583
DON'T LOOK SO SHOCKED.
WE ALWAYS LOSE THESE THINGS.

43:26.583 --> 43:28.834
YOU BASTARDS
AND YOUR FREE SPEECH.

43:28.834 --> 43:32.583
[ CHUCKLES ] MY BOSS NEVER
LETS ME SAY ANYTHING.

43:32.583 --> 43:34.291
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT --

43:34.291 --> 43:36.792
I WILL AGREE TO DROPPING
THE INJUNCTION,

43:36.792 --> 43:39.875
WHICH WILL SAVE US DAYS
OF COURTROOM ARGUMENTS

43:39.875 --> 43:41.625
AND A BOATLOAD
OF LEGAL FEES,

43:41.625 --> 43:45.417
IF WE CAN AGREE
ON SOME SIMPLE GROUND RULES

43:45.417 --> 43:47.458
ON HOW YOU PUBLISH
THAT DOCUMENT.

43:47.458 --> 43:48.667
"GROUND RULES."

43:48.667 --> 43:50.333
WE'RE NOT GONNA HAVE
ANY GROUND RULES.

43:50.333 --> 43:53.959
MY ONLY GOAL HERE IS TO AVOID
COMPROMISING AN INVESTIGATION

43:53.959 --> 43:56.458
OF A MASS MURDERER...

43:56.458 --> 43:59.709
WHO COULD HURT
A LOT MORE PEOPLE.

43:59.709 --> 44:02.667
GIVE ME JUST A SECOND,
WILL YOU, FRANK?

44:10.542 --> 44:12.750
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU GOT THOSE ASSHOLES

44:12.750 --> 44:15.291
TO PUBLISH THE MANIFESTO
WITHOUT THE VICTIMS' NAMES

44:15.291 --> 44:18.291
AND AS A PAGE-3 STORY.

44:18.291 --> 44:19.750
NO SENSE HYPING IT.

44:19.750 --> 44:22.250
IT MIGHT JUST INSPIRE THE KILLER
TO GREATER HEIGHTS.

44:22.250 --> 44:23.750
WAIT.

44:23.750 --> 44:25.458
IT'S QUIET HERE...

44:25.458 --> 44:27.750
PEACEFUL.

44:27.750 --> 44:29.750
IT'S A GOOD SPOT.

44:29.750 --> 44:31.792
FOR WHAT?

44:31.792 --> 44:33.458
IT'S 1:00.

44:36.166 --> 44:38.166
SO IT IS.

44:41.750 --> 44:44.041
I BROUGHT MY OWN SANDWICH.

44:47.542 --> 44:50.166
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T LIKE
THE QUIET, MORGAN.

44:50.166 --> 44:51.750
I DIDN'T.

44:51.750 --> 44:53.166
I DON'T.

44:55.458 --> 44:58.500
WHEN I'M ALONE
AND IT'S QUIET, I GET SCARED...

44:58.500 --> 45:00.583
SHITLESS,

45:00.583 --> 45:05.667
LIKE I START HEARING
WHAT'S REALLY GOING ON INSIDE.

45:05.667 --> 45:08.166
I SEE.

45:08.166 --> 45:09.875
SO IF IT'S ALL THE SAME
TO YOU,

45:09.875 --> 45:12.792
MAYBE I CAN JUST PRACTICE
WHEN YOU'RE AROUND.

45:12.792 --> 45:15.500
OKAY.

45:15.500 --> 45:17.667
'CAUSE WHEN YOU'RE AROUND,

45:17.667 --> 45:20.917
I KIND OF FEEL LIKE I CAN DEAL
WITH ANYTHING, YOU KNOW?

45:22.417 --> 45:25.875
LIKE WHAT HAPPENED TO ME --

45:25.875 --> 45:29.542
I DON'T HAVE TO RUN FROM IT.

45:29.542 --> 45:33.166
I DON'T HAVE TO JUMP INTO BED
WITH SOME GUY AND HIDE THERE.

45:36.834 --> 45:38.917
YOU GIVE ME STRENGTH.

45:46.542 --> 45:49.542
I'M KIND OF
OPENING UP HERE.

45:49.542 --> 45:53.333
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

45:53.333 --> 45:56.083
I DON'T KNOW.

45:56.083 --> 46:00.458
YOU'RE THE FUCKING ZEN MASTER.
FIGURE IT OUT.

46:04.041 --> 46:06.250
MORGAN...

46:06.250 --> 46:08.083
I'VE GOT PLAQUE
IN MY ARTERIES.

46:08.083 --> 46:10.083
I KNOW THE LYRICS
TO ELEVATOR MUSIC.

46:10.083 --> 46:12.208
MY HAIR ISN'T GETTING
ANY THICKER.

46:49.750 --> 46:51.458
YOU'RE GONNA DO GREAT
UP THERE.

46:51.458 --> 46:53.166
YOU JUST HAVE
TO REMEMBER SOMETHING --

46:53.166 --> 46:55.041
THEY'RE MORE FRIGHTENED
THAN YOU ARE.

46:55.041 --> 46:56.125
NO, THEY'RE NOT.

46:56.125 --> 46:57.625
ARE SO.

46:57.625 --> 46:59.834
YOU'RE GONNA BE STARING AT THEM
THE WHOLE TIME.

46:59.834 --> 47:01.625
IF ONE OF THOSE UNSUSPECTING
MOMS OR DADS

47:01.625 --> 47:03.959
DOES SOMETHING EMBARRASSING
WHILE YOU'RE UP ON STAGE...

47:03.959 --> 47:04.834
LIKE PICK THEIR NOSE?

47:04.834 --> 47:06.667
...YOU'RE GONNA BE THE ONE
WHO SEES IT.

47:06.667 --> 47:08.417
YEAH.

47:08.417 --> 47:09.250
NOW THAT'S POWER.

47:09.250 --> 47:12.291
NOW GO HAVE FUN.

47:13.792 --> 47:17.000
DEXTER, OVER HERE.
WE SAVED YOU A SEAT.

47:17.000 --> 47:18.333
THANKS, GUYS.

47:23.500 --> 47:28.166
THERE YOU GO -- $18,000.

47:28.166 --> 47:30.291
I'LL SEND A TRUCK
FOR THE PIECE TOMORROW.

47:30.291 --> 47:32.000
I AM TELLING YOU, LILA,

47:32.000 --> 47:35.959
THIS IS GOING TO CREATE
A CRITICAL MASS FOR YOU.

47:37.375 --> 47:39.667
Masuka: ACCORDING TO THE
PSYCHOLINGUISTIC ANALYSIS

47:39.667 --> 47:41.083
OF THE MANIFESTO,

47:41.083 --> 47:45.166
OUR KILLER IS A WHITE MALE
IN HIS 50s.

47:45.166 --> 47:46.417
WHAT ELSE?

47:46.417 --> 47:49.583
UH, THE KILLER
HAS NO GIRLFRIENDS

47:49.583 --> 47:51.500
AND CONSIDERS HIMSELF
A GOOD CATHOLIC.

47:51.500 --> 47:52.792
Batista: HOLD ON.
HOLD ON. HOLD ON.

47:52.792 --> 47:54.667
HOW CAN YOU TELL ALL THAT
BY PUTTING WORDS IN A COMPUTER?

47:54.667 --> 47:56.792
I DON'T KNOW, DUDE.
IT'S SCIENCE.

47:56.792 --> 47:58.125
HOW 'BOUT COMMON SENSE?

47:58.125 --> 48:00.917
I THINK THE GUY THAT
WE'RE LOOKING FOR IS
PISSED OFF AT GOD,

48:00.917 --> 48:02.583
AND THAT'S WHY
HE KILLS PEOPLE.

48:02.583 --> 48:05.458
REALLY? I ACTUALLY FOUND HIM
VERY POLITICALLY MOTIVATED.

48:05.458 --> 48:07.291
YEAH, LIKE A MODERN-DAY
REVOLUTIONARY.

48:07.291 --> 48:10.417
WHICH WOULD SUGGEST THAT
HE'S KILLING FOR SOCIAL CHANGE.

48:10.417 --> 48:13.083
[ ALL TALKING ]

48:17.750 --> 48:19.709
THIS IS WHAT HE WANTS.

48:19.709 --> 48:20.875
WHAT'S THAT?

48:20.875 --> 48:23.500
CONFUSION, CHAOS --

48:23.500 --> 48:26.250
IT'S WHAT THE KILLER WANTS.

48:26.250 --> 48:28.667
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN AN INTENSELY
PRIVATE FIGURE,

48:28.667 --> 48:30.709
DISPATCHING VICTIMS SILENTLY.

48:30.709 --> 48:33.709
NOW HE'S SUDDENLY A MEDIA WHORE?
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

48:33.709 --> 48:35.709
HE'S CREATING
A CLUSTERFUCK.

48:35.709 --> 48:37.875
VERY GOOD, OFFICER MORGAN.

48:37.875 --> 48:39.792
THE KILLER'S MAKING US
CHASE OUR TAILS.

48:39.792 --> 48:41.542
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

48:59.667 --> 49:01.083
HE KNOWS HOW WE WORK.

49:01.083 --> 49:03.125
LOOK HOW HE HITS
EVERY MAJOR THEME --

49:03.125 --> 49:05.500
POLITICAL,
ENVIRONMENTAL, RELIGIOUS.

49:05.500 --> 49:09.625
IN ONE SECTION, HE MANAGES TO
WEAVE TOGETHER JULIUS CAESAR,

49:09.625 --> 49:12.542
BERLIN, GERMANY, THE PITTSBURGH
STEELERS, AND GANDHI.

49:12.542 --> 49:13.917
IT'S SCATTERSHOT.

49:13.917 --> 49:16.417
HE KNEW THAT THIS WOULD
SEND US SCURRYING

49:16.417 --> 49:17.834
LIKE SQUIRRELS FOR NUTS.

49:17.834 --> 49:21.417
YEAH, BUT TO SUGGEST THAT
HE MIGHT BE ONE OF US --

49:21.417 --> 49:23.250
HOW CAN YOU BE SURE?

49:27.125 --> 49:30.583
HI, I'M CODY,
AND I RESEARCHED SAUDI ARABIA

49:30.583 --> 49:32.792
FOR MY CULTURAL REPORT.

49:32.792 --> 49:34.041
MY BOARD IS COVERED IN SAND

49:34.041 --> 49:37.291
BECAUSE SAUDI ARABIA
IS ONE BIG DESERT.

49:37.291 --> 49:42.583
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]
AS YOU CAN SEE, I USED COFFEE
BEANS TO WRITE "SAUDI ARABIA."

49:42.583 --> 49:45.083
ARABIC COFFEE IS VERY FAMOUS.

49:45.083 --> 49:47.000
I'M A LITTLE CONFUSED.

49:47.000 --> 49:49.875
LILA IS THE ONE SHOWING ME
HOW TO TAKE CONTROL,

49:49.875 --> 49:53.458
STOP KILLING,
GET MY LIFE CLEAN.

49:53.458 --> 49:56.375
BUT THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
SINCE I WENT INTO RECOVERY

49:56.375 --> 49:59.125
THAT I ACTUALLY  FEEL  CLEAN.

49:59.125 --> 50:01.959
THE CHILDREN IN SAUDI ARABIA
ARE JUST LIKE US,

50:01.959 --> 50:03.000
BECAUSE THEY...

50:26.917 --> 50:29.792
THIS IS THE SAUDI ARABIAN FLAG.

50:31.417 --> 50:36.041
THE ARABIC LETTERS MEAN
"THERE IS NO GOD EXCEPT ALLAH."

50:47.917 --> 50:50.959
DO YOU KNOW HOW TOUGH IT IS
FOR A WOMAN IN SAUDI ARABIA?

50:50.959 --> 50:54.000
THEY CAN'T DRIVE OR HAVE
POWERFUL JOBS.

51:00.000 --> 51:02.166
OR GET THIS -- THEY CAN'T EVEN
GO TO THE MOVIES

51:02.166 --> 51:03.542
WITHOUT MEN'S PERMISSION.

51:03.542 --> 51:07.625
AFTER THEY TURN 12, THEY HAVE
TO WEAR LONG BLACK SLEEVES,

51:07.625 --> 51:11.917
AND THEY CAN'T HARDLY EVEN TALK
TO MEN UNTIL THEY GET MARRIED.

51:20.250 --> 51:21.625
THE NEW KING, ABDULLAH,

51:21.625 --> 51:23.709
IS TRYING TO CHANGE
SOME OLD BAD RULES,

51:23.709 --> 51:25.667
SO WOMEN CAN DO MORE THINGS...

51:28.917 --> 51:31.000
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR LISTENING.

51:31.000 --> 51:33.834
OR, AS THEY SAY
IN ARABIC, "SHOKRAN."

51:33.834 --> 51:37.083
[ APPLAUSE ]

51:55.000 --> 51:59.041
[ BELL RINGS ]

51:59.041 --> 52:01.542
I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW CALM
YOU WERE UP THERE.

52:01.542 --> 52:04.250
YEAH, YOU WERE LIKE
A PROFESSIONAL TALKER.

52:04.250 --> 52:05.959
YOU WERE PRETTY GOOD.

52:05.959 --> 52:10.083
CAN DEXTER COME
FOR ICE CREAM WITH US?

52:10.083 --> 52:12.000
CAN HE, MOM, PLEASE?

52:12.000 --> 52:15.625
UH...SURE,
DEXTER CAN JOIN US.

52:15.625 --> 52:16.667
I WOULDN'T MISS IT.

52:16.667 --> 52:18.792
MAYBE THEY'LL HAVE SOME
DELICIOUS SAUDI FLAVORS,

52:18.792 --> 52:20.291
LIKE SAND OR OIL.

52:20.291 --> 52:24.125
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]
HANG ON A SEC, GUYS.

52:24.125 --> 52:25.834
HELLO.

52:28.709 --> 52:30.458
ARE YOU HURT?

52:30.458 --> 52:33.959
O-OKAY, OKAY.
I'M COMING NOW.

52:36.667 --> 52:37.959
I KNOW. ME TOO.

52:42.959 --> 52:45.500
COME ON, KIDS.
DEXTER WON'T BE JOINING US.

52:45.500 --> 52:46.875
RITA, IT'S AN EMERGENCY.

52:46.875 --> 52:48.959
LOOK, I'M SO SORRY,
YOU GUYS.

52:48.959 --> 52:50.250
I'M GONNA MAKE IT UP
TO YOU,

52:50.250 --> 52:52.000
BUT I GOT TO HELP A FRIEND
WHO'S IN TROUBLE.

52:52.000 --> 52:53.750
THERE WAS A FIRE
AT HER PLACE.

52:53.750 --> 52:54.792
I'M SO SORRY.

52:54.792 --> 52:58.125
HEY, LET'S GO.

53:07.000 --> 53:08.959
[ EXTINGUISHER HISSING ]

53:17.667 --> 53:18.959
[ HISSING CONTINUES ]

53:21.291 --> 53:22.709
DEXTER.

53:25.875 --> 53:27.041
WHAT HAPPENED?

53:27.041 --> 53:28.709
[ SNIFFLES ]

53:28.709 --> 53:32.166
I WAS WORKING ON MY PIECE
WITH THE BLOWTORCH,

53:32.166 --> 53:34.333
AND IT JUST CAUGHT FIRE.
I WAS SO SCARED.

53:34.333 --> 53:35.500
OH, I GUESS SO.

53:37.875 --> 53:39.583
[ SNIFFLES ]

53:39.583 --> 53:41.959
[ SIGHS ]

53:41.959 --> 53:44.542
PROMISE ME THAT YOU WON'T
LEAVE ME,

53:44.542 --> 53:46.834
THAT YOU WON'T GO ANYWHERE.

53:46.834 --> 53:49.250
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

54:00.542 --> 54:03.166
HEY, YOU GOT
YOUR LIGHT FIXED.
